            <person xml:id="pers0929">
               <p>A native of <placeName>Yorkshire</placeName>, Hanson became a <seg
                     ana="itinerancy">traveling preacher</seg> about <date when="1764">1764</date>.
                  He appears in the Minutes of Conference from <date when="1765">1765</date> through
                  at least <date when="1791">1791</date>, though after <date when="1786">1786</date>
                  he is receiving support as a supernumerary (<hi rend="italic">Works</hi>, 10:304,
                  597). He retired at <placeName>Horbery</placeName>, near
                     <placeName>Wakefield</placeName>, where he died. See <hi rend="italic"
                  >DEB</hi>, 515; <hi rend="italic">EMP</hi>, 6:201–10; <hi rend="italic"
                     >Minutes</hi> (post-Wesley, <date when="1805">1805</date>), 2:270; and <hi
                     rend="italic">WHS</hi> 30 (<date when="1956">1956</date>): 127–31.</p>
            </person>
